   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3449_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>


               <address>
                  <addrLine>St. Juliot</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Boscastle</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1872-11-29">Nov 29. 1872</date>
               </dateline>

               <salute>Dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Hardy</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Many thanks to you for your very kind letter of yesterdays receipt I take the
                  <unclear reason="illegible">earliest</unclear> opportunity to <unclear
                  reason="illegible">write</unclear> a line to <unclear reason="illegible"
                  >express</unclear>
               <add place="above">to</add> you how much I welcome the plan you have drawn &amp;
                  <unclear reason="illegible">sent off</unclear> of the route probable to be taken
               by the projected <unclear reason="illegible">railway</unclear> passing
                     <choice><abbr>thru</abbr>
                  <expan>through</expan></choice>
               <placeName ref="#pl:StJuliot">St. Juliot</placeName> to <unclear reason="illegible"
                  >Launceston</unclear>; I hope to live to see it, but I fear it will <pb n="2"
                  facs="uoedh_hl_h.3449_2.jpg"/> be many years. Whoever <hi rend="underline"
                  >does</hi> live to <unclear reason="illegible">witness</unclear> its opening will
               be indeed greatly accommodated, for the present generation are any thing but right as
               to <unclear reason="illegible">locomotion</unclear>.</p>

            <p>We <hi rend="underline">all</hi> hope to see you on Wednesday the 18<hi
                  rend="superscript">th</hi> (eighteenth) of December 1872. when we hope to have the
               pleasure of your company as long as you like.</p>

            <p>The young lady, <persName ref="#ps:EmmaHardy">Miss Gifford</persName> whom you
               mention is still <pb n="3" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3449_3.jpg"/> here &amp; sends her
               regards <choice><abbr>&amp;c</abbr><expan>etc.</expan></choice> to
                        <unclear><choice><abbr>&amp;c</abbr><expan>etc.</expan></choice></unclear>
               <gap extent="two characters" reason="illegible"/>. </p>

            <closer>
               <salute>With our best remembrances</salute>
               <salute>Yours truly</salute>
               <signed>Caddell Holder</signed> T. Hardy <choice><abbr>Esq.</abbr>
                  <expan>Esquire</expan></choice>
            </closer>

            <pb n="4" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3449_4.jpg"/>

         </div>
      </body>
